              "Citations": [
                {
                  "Cited_Guidance": "ADaMIG v1.3, Section 3.1.1, Item 3: Any variable in an ADaM dataset whose name is the same as an SDTM variable must be a copy of the SDTM variable, and its label, meaning, and values must not be modified. ADaM adheres to a principle of harmonization known as \"same name, same meaning, same values.\"",
